---
import Article from "../../../layouts/Article.astro";
import KeyTakeaway from "../../../components/KeyTakeaway.astro";
import InfoBox from "../../../components/InfoBox.astro";
import ComparisonTable from "../../../components/ComparisonTable.astro";
---

<Article
  title="Best Wingspan Expansions: European, Oceania, or Asia?"
  description="Each expansion changes the game differently. Here's which to grab first."
  game="wingspan"
  gameTitle="Wingspan"
  category="Buying Guide"
  product="wingspan-food-tokens"
  publishDate="2025-05-06"
>
  <p>
    Wingspan has three major expansions, each adding birds from a different continent
    along with new mechanics. They all combine with each other and the base game,
    but they feel very different to play.
  </p>

  <KeyTakeaway answer="Oceania is the best first expansion — it improves the base game's weakest points without adding complexity. European is a close second." />

  <div class="my-8 space-y-6">
    <div class="p-6 bg-white rounded-2xl border border-bark/10 relative overflow-hidden">
      <div class="absolute top-0 right-0 px-4 py-1.5 bg-emerald-500 text-white text-xs font-bold rounded-bl-xl">#1 PICK</div>
      <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-3">
        <span class="text-3xl">🦘</span>
        <div>
          <h3 class="font-heading font-bold text-xl text-bark">Oceania Expansion</h3>
          <span class="text-xs text-bark/40">81 new birds from Australia & New Zealand</span>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-2 mb-3">
        <span class="px-2 py-0.5 bg-blue-50 text-blue-700 text-[11px] font-semibold rounded-full">New Player Mats</span>
        <span class="px-2 py-0.5 bg-emerald-50 text-emerald-700 text-[11px] font-semibold rounded-full">Nectar Resource</span>
        <span class="px-2 py-0.5 bg-purple-50 text-purple-700 text-[11px] font-semibold rounded-full">End-of-Game Nectar Scoring</span>
      </div>
      <p class="text-sm text-bark/60 mb-3">
        The new player mats are the headline feature — they replace the originals and are
        strictly better designed. Nectar is a wild food that works everywhere but gets
        scored at end of game, adding a new strategic dimension. The Oceania birds have
        refreshed powers that make every habitat row feel more active.
      </p>
      <InfoBox type="tip">
        Many players permanently replace the original player mats with the Oceania ones. They're that much better.
      </InfoBox>
    </div>

    <div class="p-6 bg-white rounded-2xl border border-bark/10 relative overflow-hidden">
      <div class="absolute top-0 right-0 px-4 py-1.5 bg-blue-500 text-white text-xs font-bold rounded-bl-xl">#2 SAFE BUY</div>
      <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-3">
        <span class="text-3xl">🏰</span>
        <div>
          <h3 class="font-heading font-bold text-xl text-bark">European Expansion</h3>
          <span class="text-xs text-bark/40">81 new birds from Europe</span>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-2 mb-3">
        <span class="px-2 py-0.5 bg-purple-50 text-purple-700 text-[11px] font-semibold rounded-full">End-of-Round Powers</span>
        <span class="px-2 py-0.5 bg-amber-50 text-amber-700 text-[11px] font-semibold rounded-full">New Bonus Cards</span>
      </div>
      <p class="text-sm text-bark/60 mb-3">
        Adds round-end triggered powers (a new timing category) and more variety to the
        bird card pool. Feels like "more Wingspan" in the best way — not a revolution,
        but a solid expansion of what's already great. The European birds have some of
        the most beautifully illustrated cards in the entire game.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="p-6 bg-white rounded-2xl border border-bark/10 relative overflow-hidden">
      <div class="absolute top-0 right-0 px-4 py-1.5 bg-amber-500 text-white text-xs font-bold rounded-bl-xl">#3 FOR VETERANS</div>
      <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-3">
        <span class="text-3xl">🏔️</span>
        <div>
          <h3 class="font-heading font-bold text-xl text-bark">Asia Expansion</h3>
          <span class="text-xs text-bark/40">90 new birds from Asia + new game modes</span>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-2 mb-3">
        <span class="px-2 py-0.5 bg-red-50 text-red-700 text-[11px] font-semibold rounded-full">Duet Mode (2P)</span>
        <span class="px-2 py-0.5 bg-blue-50 text-blue-700 text-[11px] font-semibold rounded-full">Flock Mode (6–7P)</span>
        <span class="px-2 py-0.5 bg-emerald-50 text-emerald-700 text-[11px] font-semibold rounded-full">New Board</span>
      </div>
      <p class="text-sm text-bark/60 mb-3">
        The most ambitious expansion. Duet mode gives you a dedicated 2-player experience
        on a shared map — it's almost a different game and it's excellent. Flock mode lets
        you play with up to 7 people. The Asia birds interact with the new board in unique ways.
      </p>
      <InfoBox type="info">
        If you mostly play with one other person, Asia's Duet mode alone justifies the purchase. It's widely considered the best 2-player Wingspan experience.
      </InfoBox>
    </div>
  </div>

  <ComparisonTable title="Quick Comparison">
    <table class="w-full text-sm">
      <thead>
        <tr>
          <th class="text-left p-3 bg-bark/[0.02] font-heading font-semibold text-bark/70">Feature</th>
          <th class="text-left p-3 bg-bark/[0.02] font-heading font-semibold text-bark/70">European</th>
          <th class="text-left p-3 bg-bark/[0.02] font-heading font-semibold text-bark/70">Oceania</th>
          <th class="text-left p-3 bg-bark/[0.02] font-heading font-semibold text-bark/70">Asia</th>
        </tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr class="border-t border-bark/5">
          <td class="p-3">New birds</td><td class="p-3">81</td><td class="p-3">81</td><td class="p-3">90</td>
        </tr>
        <tr class="border-t border-bark/5">
          <td class="p-3">New mechanic</td><td class="p-3">Round-end powers</td><td class="p-3">Nectar</td><td class="p-3">Duet/Flock modes</td>
        </tr>
        <tr class="border-t border-bark/5">
          <td class="p-3">Complexity added</td><td class="p-3">Low</td><td class="p-3">Low-Medium</td><td class="p-3">Medium</td>
        </tr>
        <tr class="border-t border-bark/5">
          <td class="p-3">Best for</td><td class="p-3">More variety</td><td class="p-3">Better base game</td><td class="p-3">2P or 6-7P</td>
        </tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>
  </ComparisonTable>
</Article>
